snippet: While their comments were not outwardly negative, conservative commentators, and many news outlets, suggested that South Carolina would pose a more important test.
abstract: Conservative television commentators and news outlets covering Republican presidential hopeful Mitt Romney's win in the New Hampshire primary suggest that South Carolina will pose a more important test; while their comments are not outwardly negative, they implicitly urge TV and Web viewers to stay tuned.

byline.contributor: David Carr and Noam Cohen contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: While their comments were not outwardly negative, conservative commentators, and many news outlets, suggested that South Carolina would pose a more important test.

headline.seo: After Fast Romney Win, TV Analysts Shift Focus to South Carolina
headline.main: With a Fast and Anticipated Result, TV Analysts Shift Focus to South Carolina
headline.print_headline: With a Fast and Anticipated Result, TV Analysts Shift Focus to South Carolina
